  "issue_title": "Celery 4.2.0 - 5.6.0: Exception in group nested in double chain is raising internal error",
  "issue_body": "## Checklist\ncelery -A proj report\n\nsoftware -> celery:4.2.0 (windowlicker) kombu:4.2.0 py:3.5.2\n            billiard:3.5.0.3 py-amqp:2.3.2 \nplatform -> system:Linux arch:64bit, ELF imp:CPython\nloader   -> celery.loaders.app.AppLoader\nsettings -> transport:amqp results:redis:///\n\n## Steps to reproduce\nCreate a group with failing task. Group should be nested in chain, which will be in another chain.\n\n```\n@shared_task\ndef my_failing_task(raise_error):\n    if raise_error:\n        raise Exception(\"Raising exception\")\n    return \"OK my_failing_task\"\n\n@shared_task\ndef my_task_result(p1):\n    logger.info(\"my_task_result: {}\".format(p1))\n    return \"OK my_task_result\"\n\n@shared_task\ndef on_error_task(*args, **kwargs):\n    logger.info(\"on_error_task: {}, {}\".format(args, kwargs))\n    return \"OK on_error_task\"\n\ndef create_nested_chain_with_group():\n    group_of_tasks = group(my_failing_task.si(raise_error=False), my_failing_task.si(raise_error=True))\n    return chain(group_of_tasks, my_task_result.s())\n\ndef run():\n    second_chain = chain(create_nested_chain_with_group(),\n                         my_task_result.s())\n    second_chain.link_error(on_error_task.s(\"Error caught by second_chain\"))\n    second_chain()\n```\n\nThis as expected will raise Exception('Raising exception',)\n\n## Expected behavior\n`` on_error_task `` should be run and log which task has failed\n\n## Actual behavior\n`` on_error_task `` is not runned and whole task crashes with below exception:\n\n\n```\n/libs/celery/app/trace.py:561: RuntimeWarning: Exception raised outside body: TypeError('sequence item 1: expected a bytes-like object, NoneType found',):\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/redis.py\", line 368, in on_chord_part_return\n    callback.delay([unpack(tup, decode) for tup in resl])\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/redis.py\", line 368, in <listcomp>\n    callback.delay([unpack(tup, decode) for tup in resl])\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/redis.py\", line 323, in _unpack_chord_result\n    raise ChordError('Dependency {0} raised {1!r}'.format(tid, retval))\ncelery.exceptions.ChordError: Dependency 3b405d80-90df-4426-8782-c8002ba3000d raised Exception('Raising exception',)\n\nDuring handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/redis.py\", line 374, in on_chord_part_return\n    ChordError('Callback error: {0!r}'.format(exc)),\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 220, in chord_error_from_stack\n    return backend.fail_from_current_stack(callback.id, exc=exc)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 227, in fail_from_current_stack\n    self.mark_as_failure(task_id, exc, ei.traceback)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 155, in mark_as_failure\n    traceback=traceback, request=request)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 316, in store_result\n    request=request, **kwargs)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 658, in _store_result\n    self.set(self.get_key_for_task(task_id), self.encode(meta))\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 564, in get_key_for_task\n    self.task_keyprefix, key_t(task_id), key_t(key),\nTypeError: sequence item 1: expected a bytes-like object, NoneType found\n\nDuring handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:\n\nTraceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/libs/celery/app/trace.py\", line 442, in trace_task\n    uuid, retval, task_request, publish_result,\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 146, in mark_as_done\n    self.on_chord_part_return(request, state, result)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/redis.py\", line 383, in on_chord_part_return\n    ChordError('Join error: {0!r}'.format(exc)),\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 220, in chord_error_from_stack\n    return backend.fail_from_current_stack(callback.id, exc=exc)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 227, in fail_from_current_stack\n    self.mark_as_failure(task_id, exc, ei.traceback)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 155, in mark_as_failure\n    traceback=traceback, request=request)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 316, in store_result\n    request=request, **kwargs)\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 658, in _store_result\n    self.set(self.get_key_for_task(task_id), self.encode(meta))\n  File \"/libs/celery/backends/base.py\", line 564, in get_key_for_task\n    self.task_keyprefix, key_t(task_id), key_t(key),\nTypeError: sequence item 1: expected a bytes-like object, NoneType found\n\n  exc, exc_info.traceback)))\n```\n\n",
